<br>
Graphics: The game has the best PC graphics I've ever seen. It looks like a movie, NOT a CG movie but a real life movie. Lighting effects and shadows cast are all realistic. Character animations look great and the facial expressions show all kinds of emotions.<br>
<br>
Sounds: Everything sounds realistic. The guns fire, way different things sound when they hit the grounds, the way bullets sound when they hit certain things. The list goes on and on.<br>
<br>
Gamplay: Everything seems to be interactive, you and every other character can push, and throw everything in the game. Instead of shooting you can look around the area and think of endless ways to use items to help you fight. You can push stuff in front of doors to keep people out, throw stuff down stairs so people can't follow you upstairs to name a few. You cant just hid behind anything, bullets go threw some objects and no threw others, this applies more so in HL2 than other games. <br>
<br>
The AI is great. The enemies and allies fight better than and anything I've ever seen. Your allies don't follow preset paths, they take cover or shoot or doing anything based on what they THINK is the best thing to do at that time.<br>
<br>
I think at HL2 will revolutionize the way FPS and all games in general will be made in the future.<br>
<br>
